         <abstract>
            <p>In this note we present some computational results which restrict the least odd value of $k$ such that $k \cdot 2^n + 1$ is composite for all $n \geqslant 1$ to one of 91 numbers between 3061 and 78557, inclusive. Further, we give the computational results of a relaxed problem and prove for any positive integer $r$ the existence of infinitely many odd integers $k$ such that $k \cdot 2^r + 1$ is prime but $k \cdot 2^v + 1$ is not prime for $v &lt; r$.</p>
          </abstract>
